{"title_page": "Jamaicans", "text_new": "{{short description|Citizens of Jamaica and their descendants}}\n{{other uses|Jamaican (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use Jamaican English|date=March 2012}}\n{{Infobox ethnic group \n|flag = [[File:Flag of Jamaica.svg|border|300px]]\n|flag_caption = [[Flag of Jamaica|National Flag of Jamaica]]\n|total =  {{circa}} '''4.4 million'''<br>'''2,683,707''' (2011 census)<ref>[https://issuu.com/digjamaica/docs/1_pdfsam_general_report_census_2011/112?ff 2011 Census of Population & Housing], Population by sex and Ethnic Origin by Parish (Page: 72) - Jamaica</ref> \n|popplace = Jamaica &nbsp; {{UN_Population|Jamaica}}{{UN_Population|ref}}\n|region1  = United States\n|pop1     = 800,000+\n|ref1     = <ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=ACS_13_1YR_B04003&prodType=table Results &nbsp;] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20200212212204/http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?pid=ACS_13_1YR_B04003&prodType=table |date=2020-02-12 }} American Fact Finder (US Census Bureau)</ref>\n|region3   = Canada\n|pop3      = 300,000+\n|ref3      = <ref name=\"CanadaCensus2011\">[http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/nhs-enm/2011/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=PR&Code1=01&Data=Count&SearchText=canada&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&A1=All&B1=All&Custom=&TABID=1 NHS Profile, Canada, 2011], Statistics Canada. Retrieved December 2nd, 2013</ref><ref name=jamaicans>[http://www12.statcan.ca/census-recensement/2006/dp-pd/hlt/97-562/pages/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo=PR&Code=01&Table=2&Data=Count&StartRec=1&Sort=3&Display=All&CSDFilter=5000 Ethnic origins, 2006 counts, for Canada, provinces and territories - 20% sample data], Statistics Canada (2006). Retrieved on August 11, 2008.</ref><ref>[http://www12.statcan.ca/english/census01/products/highlight/ETO/Table1.cfm?T=501&Lang=E&GV=1&GID=0 Ethnic Origins for Canada - 2001 Census]. Retrieved December 6th, 2013</ref><ref>[http://www.statcan.gc.ca/c1996-r1996/feb17-17fev/oe1ca-eo1ca-eng.htm Top 25 Ethnic Origins for Canada - 1996 Census]. Retrieved December 6th, 2013</ref>\n|region4  = United Kingdom\n|pop4     =  500,000+\n|ref4     = <ref name=\"iom.int\">{{cite web |url=https://www.iom.int/world-migration |title=World Migration |author= |date=15 January 2015 |website=iom.int}}</ref>\n|region5   = [[The Bahamas]]\n|pop5      = 5,572<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thenassauguardian.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=35308&Itemid=27 |title=The Nassau Guardian Home - The Nassau Guardian |author= |date= |website=The Nassau Guardian}}</ref>\n|region6   = Germany\n|pop6   =  1,671\n|ref6    = <ref name=\"iom.int\"/>\n|region7 = [[Trinidad and Tobago]]\n|pop7    = 15,000\n|ref7      = <ref name=\"iom.int\"/>\n|region8   = Australia\n|pop8     = 1,092\n|ref8      = <ref name=\"iom.int\"/>\n|region9   = Other\n|pop9      = ~2,000\u20135,000\n|ref9      = <ref name=\"iom.int\"/>\n}}\n\n'''Jamaicans''' are the citizens of [[Jamaica]] and their descendants in the [[Jamaican diaspora]]. Most Jamaicans are of African descent, with minorities of Europeans, East Indians, Chinese, Middle Eastern and others or mixed ancestry. The bulk of the Jamaican diaspora resides in other [[Anglophone countries]], namely [[Jamaican Australians|Australia]], [[Jamaican Canadians|Canada]], [[Jamaican Americans|United States]] and the [[British Jamaican|United Kingdom]] and, to a lesser extent, other [[Caribbean Community|Caribbean countries]] and [[Commonwealth realms]]. Outside of Anglophone countries, the largest Jamaican diaspora community lives in [[Costa Rica]], where Jamaicans make up a significant percentage of the population.\n\nAccording to the official Jamaica Population Census of 1970, ethnic origins categories in Jamaica include: [[Afro-Jamaican|Black]]; [[Chinese Jamaicans|Chinese]]; Mixed; [[Indo-Jamaicans|East Indian]]; [[White Jamaicans|White]]; and 'Other' (e.g.: Syrian or [[Lebanese Jamaicans|Lebanese]]).<ref>[https://issuu.com/digjamaica/docs/1_pdfsam_general_report_census_2011/112?ff 2011 Census of Population & Housing], Population by sex and Ethnic Origin by Parish (Page: 72) - Jamaica</ref>\n\nJamaicans of African or partial African descent made up 89.4% of the working population. Those of non-African mixed race were the second-most prominent labour group, making up 6% of the population.<ref>{{cite book |title=Jamaica Population Census 1970 |last= |first= |publisher= |year= |isbn= |location= |pages= }}</ref>\n\n==Self-identified ethnic origin==\nResponses of the 2011 official census.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://issuu.com/digjamaica/docs/1_pdfsam_general_report_census_2011/112?ff|title=2011 Census of Population & Housing, Population by sex and Ethnic Origin by Parish (P. 72)|website=issuu.com|accessdate=April 12, 2020}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:left\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\"| Ethnic origin\n! Population\n! Males\n! Females\n! Percentage\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"| [[Afro-Jamaican|Black]] ||2,471,946|| 1,226,026||1,245,920 || 92.1 \n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"|  [[Chinese Jamaican|Chinese]]||5,228 || 2,880|| 2,348|| 0.2\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"| Mixed||162,718||73,293 ||89,425 || 6.0\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"| [[Indo-Jamaicans|East Indian]] ||20,066||10,491 ||9,575 ||0.7\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"| [[White Jamaican|White]]||4,365 ||2,192 || 2,173||0.2\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"| Other ||1,898|| 970|| 928||0.1\n|-\n|colspan=\"2\"| Not Reported||17,486|| 8,638||8,848|| 0.6\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"| Total||2,683,707|| 1,324,490|| 1,359,217|| 100.0%\n|-\n| colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:left;\"|<small>2011 Jamaica census<<ref>{{cite web|url=https://issuu.com/digjamaica/docs/1_pdfsam_general_report_census_2011/112?ff|title=2011 Census of Population & Housing, Population by sex and Ethnic Origin by Parish (P. 72)|website=issuu.com|accessdate=April 12, 2020}}</ref></small> \n|}\n\n==Religion==\nMembers of Christian denominations formed TBD per cent. of those who made answer to the inquiry at the last census; non-Christian sects were TBD per cent.; and those who described themselves as of no religion TBD per cent.; whilst \"indefinite\" religions constituted TBD per cent.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | [[Religion in Jamaica|Denomination]] !! colspan=2| 2011 census<ref>{{cite web|url=https://issuu.com/digjamaica/docs/1_pdfsam_general_report_census_2011/112?ff|title=2011 Census of Population by Sex and Religious Affiliation/Denomination by Parish (P. 80)|website=issuu.com|accessdate=April 12, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! Number !! Percentage\n|- align=right\n|align=left| '''[[Christianity in Jamaica|Christian]]''' ||''' ''' ||''' '''\n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Anglicanism]] || 74,891|| \n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Baptists]] || 180,640|| \n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Brethren (religious group)|Brethren]] || 23,647|| \n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Baptists]] || 20,872|| -\n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Brethren (religious group)|Brethren]] || 9,758|| 1.0\n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Church of God in Jamaica || 129,544|| -\n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Church of God of Prophecy  ||121,400 || -\n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[New Testament Church of God]] || 192,086|| -\n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Other [[Church of God]]{{dn}} || 246,838|| -\n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Jehovah's Witnesses]] || 50,849|| 2.0\n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Methodism|Methodist]] || 43,336|| 2.0\n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Moravian Church|Moravian]] || 18,351|| \n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Pentecostalism|Pentecostal]] || 295,195|| \n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Rastafarianism|Rastafarian]] || 29,026|| \n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Revivalist (person)|Revivalist]] || 36,296|| \n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Roman Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]] || 57,946|| \n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Seventh-day Adventist Church|Seventh-day Adventist]] ||322,228|| -\n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[United and uniting churches|United Church]] || 56,360|| \n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Bah\u00e1\u02bc\u00ed Faith in Jamaica|Bah\u00e1\u02bc\u00ed]] || 269|| \n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Hinduism]] || 1,836|| -\n|- align=right\n|align=left| &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; [[Islam]] || 1,513|| -\n|- align=right\n|align=left| '''[[History of the Jews in Jamaica|Judaism]]'''|| 506|| \n|- align=right\n|align=left|Other Religion/Denomination || 169,014|| -\n|- align=right\n| align=center| '''Totals, specified religions''' || align=center| ''' ''' || align=center| '''100.00'''\n|- align=right\t\t\t\n|align=left| No Religion/Denomination  || 572,008|| -\n|- align=right\t\t\t\n|align=left| Not reported|| 60,326|| -\n|-\n! Totals, Jamaica||2,683,105 || 100.00\n|}\n\n==Diaspora==\n{{Main|Jamaican diaspora}}\nMany Jamaicans now live overseas and outside Jamaica, while many have migrated to [[English-speaking world|Anglophone]] countries, including over 400,000 Jamaicans in the [[Jamaican British|United Kingdom]], over 300,000 [[Canada]], 800,000 in the [[United States]].\n\nThere are about 30,000 Jamaicans residing in other CARICOM member including the [[Bahamas]] (5,600),{{source needed|date=June 2019}} [[Cuba]] (5,000),{{source needed|date=June 2019}} [[Antigua & Barbuda]], [[Barbados]] and [[Trinidad & Tobago]].<ref name=\"30,000 Jamaicans residing in CARICOM member states\">{{cite web|url=http://www.caricomnews.net/index.php/caricom/caricom-news/regional-news/1889-skilled-jamaicans-refused-entry-into-some-caricom-states|title=30,000 Jamaicans residing in other CARICOM member states|author=|date=|website=caricomnews.net|access-date=2014-04-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170620140951/http://www.caricomnews.net/index.php/caricom/caricom-news/regional-news/1889-skilled-jamaicans-refused-entry-into-some-caricom-states|archive-date=2017-06-20|url-status=dead}}</ref> There are also communities of Jamaican descendants in Central America, particularly [[Costa Rica]], [[Nicaragua]], and [[Panama]]. Most of Costa Rica's [[Afro-Costa Ricans | Afro-Costa Rican]] and Mulatto population, which combined represents about 7% of the total population, is of Jamaican descent.<ref>{{cite news |last=Schulman |first=Bob | title='Little Jamaica' Rocks on the Caribbean Coast of Costa Rica |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/little-jamaica-rocks-on-t_b_8100114 |work=Huffington Post|access-date=22 January 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Koch |first=Charles W. |title=JAMAICAN BLACKS AND THEIR DESCENDANTS IN COSTA RICA |journal=Social and Economic Studies |volume=26 |issue=3 |pages=339\u2013361 |location=Jamaica |publisher=Sir Arthur Lewis Institute of Social and Economic Studies, University of the West Indies |jstor=27861669 |year=1977 }}</ref>\n\n==Notable Jamaicans==\n{{main|List of Jamaicans}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Demographics of Jamaica]]\n* [[Jamaican British]]\n* [[Jamaican American]]\n* [[Jamaican Canadian]]\n* [[Jamaican Australian]]\n* [[Jamaicans in Ethiopia]]\n* [[Afro-Costa Rican]]\n* [[Afro-Nicaraguan]]\n* [[Afro-Panamanian]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Jamaican diaspora}}\n{{Demographics of Jamaica}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jamaican People}}\n[[Category:Jamaican people|*]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Jamaica]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Citizens of Jamaica and their descendants}}\n{{other uses|Jamaican (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use Jamaican English|date=March 2012}}\n{{Infobox ethnic group \n|flag = [[File:Flag of Jamaica.svg|border|300px]]\n|flag_caption = [[Flag of Jamaica|National Flag of J